{"id": "EUVD-2025-5223", "enisaUuid": "43365d39-3d95-3dd9-b1b2-f1e35d31dfe3", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Send signals asynchronously if !preemptible\n\nBPF programs can execute in all kinds of contexts and when a program\nrunning in a non-preemptible context uses the bpf_send_signal() kfunc,\nit will cause issues because this kfunc can sleep.\nChange `irqs_disabled()` to `!preemptible()`.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T02:07:34", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:36:33", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21728", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/092fc76b7ab4163e008f9cde596a58dad2108260", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/78b97783496b454435639937db3303e900a24d3f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/87c544108b612512b254c8f79aa5c0a8546e2cc4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/be42a09fe898635b0093c0c8dac1bfabe225c240", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/eeef8e65041a031bd8a747a392c14b76a123a12c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ce51eab2070e295d298f42a2f1db269cd1b56d55", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e306eaaa3d78b462db5f5b11e0171f9d2b6ca3f4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/feba1308bc5e8e04cee751d39fae8a9b407a9034", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00028.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/05/msg00030.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21728", "GHSA-f47w-fp34-vr9h"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "04c2e3bb-650b-3831-99ce-2a60f343481e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.179"}, {"id": "1db03fd1-9b3b-3527-9c59-64e3dd23ff1c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fd29a0242f86b2d95ad666aa9f92a3d0f7bfdab6 <feba1308bc5e8e04cee751d39fae8a9b407a9034"}, {"id": "204d0fba-98dd-39a4-abfa-ae831ec69d79", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.13"}, {"id": "232f744c-2303-3600-b7e4-1d10bd9b84a9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7930d01afb7